%T and %M do not work with the /target command; however they should work in other circumstances.  I use %M a lot for social buttons such as:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>PET ATTACK Social</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
/emote points at %T<br>
/say %M, %T has angered your master, rise up and kill it!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>PET Health Social</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
/say %M, how are you feeling today?<br>
/pet health<br>
<br>
